**No, you don't need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` on .NET 10.** That property is only for .NET 9 and earlier.

On .NET 10, use the native MTP mode by adding a `test` section to your `global.json`:

```json
{
  "sdk": {
    "version": "10.0.100"
  },
  "test": {
    "runner": "Microsoft.Testing.Platform"
  }
}
```

**Key differences from the .NET 9 approach:**

| .NET 9 (old) | .NET 10 (new) |
|---|---|
| `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in Directory.Build.props | `"test": { "runner": "Microsoft.Testing.Platform" }` in global.json |
| MTP args require `--` separator: `dotnet test -- --report-trx` | Args pass directly: `dotnet test --report-trx` |

